<p>An epic inside look at the high-stakes battle to save the global economy from entering another Great Depression.</p>


<p>Three central characters in this retrospective, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7098979-on-the-brink" target="_blank"><strong>Hank Paulson<.strong><a/>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25622135-the-courage-to-act" target="_blank"><strong>Ben Bernanke</strong></a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19524269-stress-test" target="_blank"><strong>Tim Geithner</strong></a>, have since offered their own insights into this historic financial rescue, which indicates that this crisis was indeed To Big to Fail.</p>

<p>For an alternate view of the causes of The Great Recession, check out <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/167949095" target="_blank"><strong>The Big Short</strong></a> by Michael Lewis.</p>
